                <note rend="inline" type="source">667.003/163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the High
                        Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-09T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1921—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. Your 272 November 21, 5 PM and your despatch 131 April 8, 1921.<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d874fn32">The latter not printed.</note> You may inform your Allied
                    Colleagues that having in view the present conditions at Constantinople,
                    Department, as a temporary measure, without prejudice to our rights and without
                    establishing a precedent for any other taxes, consents to Commissioner’s request
                    that the municipal taxes mentioned in your said despatch and stated to be
                    necessary for the maintenance of sanitary services be applied to American
                    citizens with the understanding that such services shall be under non-Turkish
                    financial and technical supervision, that the taxes shall be equally applied to
                    all foreigners and that collection shall be effected with the help of
                    interallied police.</p>
                <p>Keep Department fully informed by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
